</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis fulva" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis fulva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
morphologically resembles 
<taxonomicName genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. menehune" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="menehune">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. menehune</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. ramealis" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="ramealis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. ramealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They can be distinguished based on several morphological differences. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R.H.Petersen" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Desjardin, Halling &amp; Hemmes" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis menehune" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="menehune">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis menehune</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a longer stipe (15-60 mm length), denser lamellae, and larger basidiospores (7.5-9.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.5-4.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" author="Desjardin, DE" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="166 - 176" refId="B10" refString="Desjardin, DE, Halling, RE, Hemmes, DE, 1999. Agaricales of the Hawaiian Islands. 5. The genera Rhodocollybia and Gymnopus. Mycologia 91 (1): 166 - 176, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" title="Agaricales of the Hawaiian Islands. 5. The genera Rhodocollybia and Gymnopus." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" volume="91" year="1999">Desjardin et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis ramealis" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ramealis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis ramealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a smaller basidiocarp (2-20 mm), shorter basidiospores (7.8-11 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-4 mm) and different type of pileipellis (
<taxonomicName genus="Rameales" lsidName="Rameales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Rameales</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-structure) (
<bibRefCitation author="Noordeloos, ME" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia-Molecular Phylogeny and Evolution of Fungi" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="31 - 49" refId="B38" refString="Noordeloos, ME, 1983. Notulae as Floram agaricinam neerlandicam - I-III. Marasmiellus, Macrocystidia and Rhodocybe. Persoonia-Molecular Phylogeny and Evolution of Fungi 12: 31 - 49" title="Notulae as Floram agaricinam neerlandicam - I-III. Marasmiellus, Macrocystidia and Rhodocybe." volume="12" year="1983">Noordeloos 1983</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Desjardin, DE" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="141 - 148" refId="B9" refString="Desjardin, DE, Halling, RE, Perry, BA, 1997. Gymnopus villosipes -a common collybioid agaric from California. Mycotaxon 64: 141 - 148" title="Gymnopus villosipes - a common collybioid agaric from California." volume="64" year="1997">Desjardin et al. 1997</bibRefCitation>
). Phylogenetically, 
<taxonomicName genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. fulva" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. fulva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. ramulicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="ramulicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. ramulicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="T. H. Li &amp; S. F. Deng" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis ramulicola" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ramulicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis ramulicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having a more yellowish pileus, fewer lamellae (9-12) that are brighter in color, a more reddish and thicker stipe (2-3 mm), and smaller sized cheilocystidia (23-27 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-6 mm) (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5248/131.663" author="Deng, SF" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="663 - 670" refId="B6" refString="Deng, SF, Li, TH, Jiang, ZD, Song, B, 2016. Gymnopus ramulicola sp. nov., a pinkish species from southern China. Mycotaxon 131 (3): 663 - 670, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5248/131.663" title="Gymnopus ramulicola sp. nov., a pinkish species from southern China." url="https://doi.org/10.5248/131.663" volume="131" year="2016">Deng et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
